      "content": "it's not just a \"wrong path\" though. you don't get it. it's the foundation. everything i've done, every connection i've made, was based on that work. now that it's gone, the person they knew is gone too. i feel like a ghost walking through a life that doesn't belong to me anymore. it's exhausting to keep performing this version of \"me\" when there's nothing behind the mask. it just feels like the most logical thing is to just... stop. to let the quiet take over so i don't have to keep pretending.",
